Description: Fraghment of neck and rising round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp with winged caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Sosikles. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX L207.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (241)
